 -- Ricardo Mones <mones@debian.org>  Mon, 17 Jun 2013 18:40:35 +0200

claws-mail (3.9.1-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * New upstream release
  - In this release all the plugins formerly know as extra-plugins
    were incorporated in the main source code tree. Some of them
    were also dropped in the process: dillo viewer (removed from
    packaging time ago), html2-viewer and trayicon plugin.
  * control, *trayicon*, manpages/*trayicon*, manpages/Makefile
  - Remove trayicon plugin, superseded by notification plugin
  - Remove --disable-dillo flag, not needed anymore
  * control, rules, manpages/Makefile, *-extra-plugins,
    *-acpi-notifier.*, *-address-keeper.*, *-archiver-plugin.*,
    *-attach-remover.*, *-attach-warner.*, *-bsfilter-plugin.*,
    *-clamd-plugin.*, *-fancy-plugin.*, *-feeds-reader.*,
    *-fetchinfo-plugin.*, *-gdata-plugin.*, *-newmail-plugin.*,
    *-mailmbox-plugin.*, *-multi-notifier.*, *-tnef-parser.*,
    *-perl-filter.*, *-pdf-viewer.*, *-python-plugin.*,
    *-spam-report.*, *-vcalendar-plugin.*
  - Migrate surviving extra-plugins, manpages converted from docbook
    SGML to XML and updated
  - Keep extra-plugins meta-package to ease transition, added Breaks
    and/or Replaces with all previous versions
  - Expand Build-Depends to enable building of all plugins
  * copyright
  - Updated years

 -- Ricardo Mones <mones@debian.org>  Tue, 07 May 2013 23:55:27 +0200

