 -- Ricardo Mones <mones@aic.uniovi.es>  Mon,  6 Feb 2006 22:58:21 +0100

sylpheed-claws-gtk2 (1.9.100-2) unstable; urgency=low

  * debian/rules
  - Fixed .desktop file name. Closes: #344188
  * debian/control
  - Fixed xlibs-dev Build-Dep. Closes: #346916

 -- Ricardo Mones <mones@aic.uniovi.es>  Mon,  9 Jan 2006 08:53:11 +0100

sylpheed-claws-gtk2 (1.9.100-1.1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Non-maintainer upload with permission of the maintainer.
  * Use -Wl,--as-needed when linking, to prevent sylpheed-claws from picking
    up dependencies on a large number of dependencies it doesn't use; this
    appears to be the only reasonable way to drop these dependencies when
    using libtool convenience libraries.  Closes: #340729.

 -- Steve Langasek <vorlon@debian.org>  Fri, 25 Nov 2005 01:41:28 -0800

sylpheed-claws-gtk2 (1.9.100-1) unstable; urgency=high

  * New upstream release.
  - Buffer overflow on import fixed (Closes: #339529)
  - IMAP code has been heavily fixed (Closes: #325082, #329196, #324667)
    See www.thewildbeast.co.uk/sylpheed-claws/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=803
    and duplicates.
  - Translation for pt_BR updated (Closes: #329040)
  * debian/control
  - Building with libreadline5-dev now, required libetpan-dev >= 0.40.
  - Fixed Recommends line for metamail and others (Closes: #336163)
  * debian/rules
  - Upstream manpage and binary names have changed.
  * debian/docs
  - Some documents have changed their name.
  * debian/patches/01configure.patch
  - Renamed and regenerated (name changes made it invalid).
  * debian/control, debian/rules, debian/patches/00list,*.dpatch
  - Patch management using dpatch.make

 -- Ricardo Mones <mones@aic.uniovi.es>  Sat, 19 Nov 2005 01:04:50 +0100

